definitions.definition: A member or adherent of Cyrenaicism , the philosophical school founded by Aristippus of Cyrene and codified by Aristippus the Younger .
Synonym of Cyrenian , a person of or from Cyrene .
Synonym of Cyrenaican , a person of or from Cyrenaica , the area around Cyrene in northeastern Libya .
